  "prompt": "What is the definition of potential energy?",
  "response": "Potential energy is the stored energy an object possesses due to its position or configuration within a force field. It represents the energy an object has because of its position relative to other objects or its internal structure. For example:\n\n1. Gravitational potential energy is the energy an object has due to its height above a reference point in a gravitational field.\n\n2. Elastic potential energy is the energy stored in a stretched or compressed spring.\n\n3. Chemical potential energy is the energy stored in chemical bonds between atoms and molecules.\n\nThe amount of potential energy depends on factors like position, height, mass, and the characteristics of the force field or system.",
